
[1]amaurosis

   AMAURO'SIS, n. [Gr. obscure.]

   A loss or decay of sight, without any visible defect in the eye, except
   an immovable pupil; called also gutta serena. Sometimes the disease is
   periodical, coming on suddenly, continuing for hours or days, and then
   disappearing. It has sometimes been cured by electricity.
